---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const lastUpdated = 'May 27, 2026';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Use"
  description="Terms of Use for trust-lionel.com — the personal brand and thought leadership blog of Lionel Mosley (ahr-ki-tekt), Houston, TX."
>
  <Nav />

  <main id="main-content" class="legal-main">
    <div class="legal-header">
      <div class="legal-header-inner">
        <div class="legal-tag">Legal</div>
        <h1 class="legal-title">Terms of Use</h1>
        <p class="legal-meta">Last updated: {lastUpdated} · Governing law: State of Texas, United States</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-body">
      <div class="legal-prose">

        <h2>Acceptance of Terms</h2>
        <p>By accessing trust-lionel.com (the "Site"), you agree to be bound by these Terms of Use. If you do not agree to these terms, please do not use the Site. These terms apply to all visitors and users of the Site.</p>

        <h2>About This Site</h2>
        <p>trust-lionel.com is the personal brand and thought leadership blog of Lionel Mosley, an IT Consultant and Innovative Thought Leader operating as ahr-ki-tekt, based in Houston, Texas. The Site publishes original articles, frameworks, and analysis related to enterprise IT, cybersecurity, cloud infrastructure, and technology strategy.</p>

        <h2>Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p>All content published on this Site — including but not limited to articles, posts, analyses, frameworks, graphics, code examples, and the site design — is the intellectual property of Lionel Mosley and is protected under United States copyright law and applicable international treaties.</p>
        <p>All Rights Reserved. No content from this Site may be reproduced, distributed, modified, published, or transmitted in any form or by any means — electronic, mechanical, photocopying, recording, or otherwise — without the prior written permission of Lionel Mosley.</p>
        <p>Permitted uses without written permission: sharing a link to any page on this Site; quoting brief excerpts (under 50 words) in commentary, criticism, or news reporting, with clear attribution to Lionel Mosley and a link to the original post.</p>

        <h2>No Professional Advice</h2>
        <p>The content published on this Site is provided for informational and educational purposes only. Nothing on this Site constitutes legal advice, financial advice, investment advice, or professional IT consulting services.</p>
        <p>Framework references, security guidance, and technical recommendations on this Site reflect the author's professional perspective and analysis. They do not constitute a client engagement. Organizations should engage qualified professionals before making technology, security, or compliance decisions.</p>

        <h2>Accuracy and Currency</h2>
        <p>Lionel Mosley makes reasonable efforts to ensure the accuracy of content published on this Site. However, the IT, cybersecurity, and technology landscape changes rapidly. Content may become outdated. No warranty is made as to the completeness, accuracy, or currency of any information on this Site.</p>

        <h2>External Links</h2>
        <p>This Site contains links to external websites including GitHub, CISA, NIST, LinkedIn, and other third-party resources. These links are provided for reference and convenience. Lionel Mosley does not endorse, control, or accept responsibility for the content, privacy practices, or availability of any linked external site.</p>

        <h2>Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
        <p>This Site is provided "as is" and "as available" without warranties of any kind, express or implied, including but not limited to warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, or non-infringement. Lionel Mosley does not warrant that the Site will be uninterrupted, error-free, or free of viruses or other harmful components.</p>

        <h2>Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>To the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, Lionel Mosley shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages arising from your use of, or inability to use, this Site or its content — even if advised of the possibility of such damages.</p>

        <h2>Governing Law</h2>
        <p>These Terms of Use are governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the State of Texas, United States, without regard to its conflict of law principles. Any dispute arising from these terms or your use of this Site shall be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts located in Texas.</p>

        <h2>Changes to These Terms</h2>
        <p>These Terms of Use may be updated at any time. Changes are effective upon posting to this page. The "Last updated" date at the top of this page reflects the date of the most recent revision. Continued use of the Site after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated terms.</p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>Questions about these Terms of Use may be directed to Lionel Mosley via <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/lionelmosley" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">LinkedIn</a> or through <a href="https://github.com/trust-lionel" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a>.</p>

      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal-main {
    min-height: 60vh;
  }

  .legal-header {
    background: var(--color-bg-header);
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
    padding: 3.5rem 2rem 3rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .legal-header::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background-image:
      linear-gradient(var(--grid-color) 1px, transparent 1px),
      linear-gradient(90deg, var(--grid-color) 1px, transparent 1px);
    background-size: 32px 32px;
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  .legal-header-inner {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
  }

  .legal-tag {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-accent);
    padding: 4px 12px;
    border-radius: var(--radius-pill);
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    opacity: 0.9;
  }

  .legal-title {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 2.75rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.15;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .legal-meta {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-weight: 400;
  }

  .legal-body {
    padding: 4rem 2rem;
  }

  .legal-prose {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .legal-prose h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: -0.015em;
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    margin: 2.5rem 0 0.75rem;
  }

  .legal-prose h2:first-child {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .legal-prose p {
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .legal-prose ul {
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .legal-prose li {
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 0.375rem;
  }

  .legal-prose a {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-accent) 40%, transparent);
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
    transition: text-decoration-color var(--transition);
  }

  .legal-prose a:hover {
    text-decoration-color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .legal-prose strong {
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .legal-header {
      padding: 2.5rem 1.25rem 2rem;
    }

    .legal-body {
      padding: 2.5rem 1.25rem;
    }
  }
</style>
